column1: I usually don't laugh or joke around much with other people
column2: If I am feeling depressed I can usually cheer myself up with humor
column3: If someone makes a mistake I will often tease them about it
column4: I don't have to work very hard at making other people laugh - I seem to be a naturally humorous person
column5: Even when I'm by myself I'm often amused by the absurdities of life
column6: People are never offended or hurt by my sense of humor
column7: I will often get carried away in putting myself down if it makes my family or friends laugh
column8: I rarely make other people laugh by telling funny stories about myself
column9: When telling jokes or saying funny things I am usually not very concerned about how other people are taking it
column10: I laugh and joke a lot with my closest friends
column11: My humorous outlook on life keeps me from getting overly upset or depressed about things
column12: I don't often say funny things to put myself down
column13: I usually don't like to tell jokes or amuse people
column14: Sometimes I think of something that is so funny that I can't stop myself from saying it even if it is not appropriate for the situation
column15: I often go overboard in putting myself down when I am making jokes or trying to be funny
column17: If I am feeling sad or upset I usually lose my sense of humor
column18: I never participate in laughing at others even if all my friends are doing it
column19: When I am with friends or family I often seem to be the one that other people make fun of or joke about
column20: I don't often joke around with my friends
column21: If I don't like someone I often use humor or teasing to put them down
column22: If I am having problems or feeling unhappy I often cover it up by joking around so that even my closest friends don't know how I really feel
column23: I usually can't think of witty things to say when I'm with other people
column24: Letting others laugh at me is my way of keeping my friends and family in good spirits
